{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b3e220e2-59b1-45ed-84cc-514dba62f9b8","content":"MSTest v3 **no longer supports `.testsettings` files**. You need to migrate the settings into a `.runsettings` file. Here's what your `local.testsettings` configures and how each part maps:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `TestTimeout` (30s) | `<MSTest><TestTimeout>` |\n| Code coverage collector | `<DataCollectors>` section |\n| Assembly resolution | No longer needed (MSTest v3 handles this) |\n\nLet me create the `.runsettings` file and wire it up:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01VKpxoERWwaKUMqh9L6JNVM","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Creating runsettings migration"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_013JbgFtitcuZV4bB8mT6RKB","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-95086ac3554a4e7ea5b2830251c0e7c4/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n  </MSTest>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n        uri=\"datacollector://microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n        assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.dll\">\n      </DataCollector>\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-95086ac3554a4e7ea5b2830251c0e7c4/local.runsettings."}],"interactionId":"45ae95b1-fc0f-42ed-8825-09781ced13e6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has:\n\n1. A `.testsettings` file with:\n   - Assembly resolution / deployment config\n   - A test timeout of 30000ms (30s)\n   - A code coverage data collector\n\n2. A `.csproj` already referencing MSTest v3 (3.8.0)\n\nMSTest v3 dropped support for `.testsettings` files. The user needs to migrate these settings to a `.runsettings` file and/or MSTest v3 attributes/configuration.\n\nLet me explain how to migrate each setting:\n\n1. **Test timeout**: In MSTest v3, you can set a default timeout via `.runsettings` under `<MSTest><TestTimeout>` or use `[Timeout]` attribute on individual tests.\n\n\n2. **Code coverage data collector**: This goes into a `.runsettings` file under `<DataCollectionRunSettings><DataCollectors>`.\n3. **Assembly resolution / deployment**: MSTest v3 handles deployment differently. The `<DeploymentItem>` attribute still works, but the `.testsettings` deployment config is no longer read. In `.runsettings`, you can configure `<MSTest><DeployTestSourceDependencies>`.\n\nNow I'll create the `.runsettings` file and update the `.csproj` to reference it.","outputTokens":754,"requestId":"603D:125080:26EDD1F:296343E:6A0493B1"},"id":"dde4cbbf-7c5a-482b-b22f-93564e2cc7b9","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:07:41.489Z","parentId":"745209b8-48f6-4b85-aa00-242da0d53c0b"}
